 There was a table set out under a tree in front of the house, and the March Hare and the Hatter before it. A Dormouse was resting from between them, fast asleep, and the two were placing their elbows on it, and talking over its head.
The above exercise can make your ear more accustomed to the sounds of the words and "deaden" your ability to hear the difference in the sounds of homophones.
# Training in speaking
